  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed but all credibility factor gaps remain. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). Decision: Not accepted. NOTE: UQ was completed via Monte Carlo sampling across inlet boundary conditions and fluid viscosity; we plan to extend with sensitivity analysis in a follow-on study to identify dominant input drivers, but that artifact has not yet been produced.",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-cfd-hemolysis-prediction",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v2",
